The paper deals with a constrained least-squares regression problem, which is a numerical optimization problem. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) category. The paper also employs a randomized Hadamard transform, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and signal processing, suggesting that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. The paper presents a novel random projection type result, which could be of independent interest and therefore could belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) category. The paper also discusses the accuracy of the algorithm, which could be related to information theory (cs.IT) and the experimental evaluation of the algorithm, which could be related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
